# Windows Shell Commands

The user runs Windows PowerShell. Do not use Unix-style `curl | node` pipes to test APIs — they hang and abort with exit code -1 because PowerShell's `curl` is an alias for `Invoke-WebRequest`, not real curl.

Use one of these instead:

```powershell
node --input-type=module -e "const j = await (await fetch('http://localhost:3000/api/...')).json(); console.log(j);"
```

```powershell
curl.exe -s "http://localhost:3000/api/..."
```

Never blame the user for failures caused by shell commands the agent chose to run.
